{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"symbolKind":"property","title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","title":"MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"overlayBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"}}}